      "category": "researcher",
      "content": "I discovered that due to an outdated atlassian software instance, I was able to exploit an SSRF vulnerability in confluence and was able to perform several actions such as bypass any firewall/protection solutions, was able to perform XSPA through assessing the response times for ports, access Internal DoD Servers and internal services.\n\nI discuss the vulnerabilities exploited in my write which you can find here, https://medium.com/bugbountywriteup/piercing-the-veil-server-side-request-forgery-to-niprnet-access-c358fd5e249a",
